      <div class="tc-segment" data-id="goodwill" style="width: 27.8%; background: #24292F; border-right: 2px solid #FFF; transition: opacity 0.3s ease;"></div>
      <div class="tc-segment" data-id="ip" style="width: 8.6%; background: #FFC52F; border-right: 2px solid #FFF; transition: opacity 0.3s ease;"></div>
      <div class="tc-segment" data-id="assets" style="width: 3.4%; background: #D1D5DB; border-right: 2px solid #FFF; transition: opacity 0.3s ease;"></div>
      <div class="tc-segment" data-id="licence" style="width: 0.5%; background: #20C997; transition: opacity 0.3s ease;"></div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div style="padding: 24px; min-height: 140px;">
    <div id="tc-info-panel" style="background: #F6F6F6; border-radius: 8px; padding: 20px; border-left: 6px solid #EA2D2E; transition: border-color 0.3s ease;">
      <div style="display: flex; justify-content: space-between; align-items: flex-start; margin-bottom: 8px; flex-wrap: wrap; gap: 12px;">
        <h4 id="tc-title" style="margin: 0; font-size: 1.25rem; font-weight: 700; color: #151515;">Customer Relationships</h4>
        <div style="text-align: right;">
          <div id="tc-value" style="font-size: 1.5rem; font-weight: 700; color: #151515; line-height: 1.1;">$14.20M</div>
          <div id="tc-percent" style="font-size: 0.875rem; color: #EA2D2E; font-weight: 600; margin-top: 4px;">59.7% of total value</div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <p id="tc-desc" style="margin: 0; font-size: 1rem; color: #555555; line-height: 1.6;">
        The largest portion of the acquired assets, giving dLocal immediate access to established enterprise merchants across African markets.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div style="padding: 20px 24px; background: #FFF9F9; border-top: 1px solid #FFE0E0;">
    <p style="margin: 0; font-size: 0.95rem; color: #151515; line-height: 1.7;">
      <strong style="color: #EA2D2E;">TechCabal Insight:</strong> The data reveals that customer relationships ($14.2 million) and goodwill ($6.6 million) accounted for approximately 87% of the transaction&#8217;s value. This illustrates that dLocal was primarily paying for immediate market access and regional footprint expansion, rather than underlying technical infrastructure or operational licences, which were valued at just $120,000.
    </p>
  </div>

  <script>
    document.addEventListener("DOMContentLoaded", function() {
      // Data mapping for the interactive chart
      const chartData = {
        'customer': { 
          title: 'Customer Relationships', 
          val: '$14.20M', 
          pct: '59.7%', 
          color: '#EA2D2E', 
          desc: "The largest portion of the acquired assets, giving dLocal immediate access to established enterprise merchants across African markets." 
        },
        'goodwill': { 
          title: 'Goodwill', 
          val: '$6.60M', 
          pct: '27.8%', 
          color: '#24292F', 
          desc: "Reflects expected regional synergies from integrating AZA Finance's presence with dLocal's existing payments infrastructure across Africa." 
        },
        'ip': { 
          title: 'Intellectual Property', 
          val: '$2.05M', 
          pct: '8.6%', 
          color: '#FFC52F', 
          desc: "Business intellectual property tied to AZA Finance's African operations." 
        },
        'assets': { 
          title: 'Net Identifiable Assets', 
          val: '$0.80M', 
          pct: '3.4%', 
          color: '#D1D5DB', 
          desc: "Mint Code Solutions held $791,000 in cash at the deal close, adjusted alongside minor prepaid expenses and current liabilities." 
        },
        'licence': { 
          title: 'Mint Code Licence', 
          val: '$0.12M', 
          pct: '0.5%', 
          color: '#20C997', 
          desc: "A Cameroonian payment entity licence, valued at just $120,000, giving dLocal a licenced operating entity in Cameroon." 
        }
      };

      const segments = document.querySelectorAll('.tc-segment');
      const panel = document.getElementById('tc-info-panel');
      const titleEl = document.getElementById('tc-title');
      const valueEl = document.getElementById('tc-value');
      const pctEl = document.getElementById('tc-percent');
      const descEl = document.getElementById('tc-desc');

      // Interaction Logic
      segments.forEach(seg => {
        
        // Touch & Mouse interactions
        const triggerUpdate = function() {
          const id = this.getAttribute('data-id');
          const info = chartData[id];
          
          // Update Panel content
          panel.style.borderLeftColor = info.color;
          pctEl.style.color = info.color === '#D1D5DB' ? '#555555' : info.color;
          titleEl.textContent = info.title;
          valueEl.textContent = info.val;
          pctEl.textContent = info.pct + " of total value";
          descEl.textContent = info.desc;
          
          // Dim other segments
          segments.forEach(s => s.style.opacity = '0.3');
          this.style.opacity = '1';
        };

        seg.addEventListener('mouseenter', triggerUpdate);
        seg.addEventListener('touchstart', function(e) {
          e.preventDefault(); // Prevent double firing on mobile
          triggerUpdate.call(this);
        });

        // Reset state when mouse leaves the chart container
        document.getElementById('tc-chart-container').addEventListener('mouseleave', function() {
          segments.forEach(s => s.style.opacity = '1');
        });
      });
    });
  </script>
</div>



<p>The valuation remains preliminary and could still change during the standard one-year accounting review period following the acquisition.</p>



<p>“The allocation of the purchase price for this acquisition has been prepared on a preliminary basis, and changes to the allocation to certain assets and liabilities may occur as additional information becomes available throughout the measurement period,” <a href="https://www.sec.gov/Archives/edgar/data/1846832/000184683226000019/ex_992-dloxfinancialxstate.htm" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow">dLocal noted in its report</a>.</p>



<h2 class="wp-block-heading"><strong>A strategic deal, not a financial one</strong></h2>



<p>Despite the complexity and publicity surrounding the transaction, dLocal has downplayed its immediate financial impact.</p>



<p>The company recorded $326,000 in acquisition-related costs <a href="https://www.sec.gov/Archives/edgar/data/1846832/000184683226000019/ex_992-dloxfinancialxstate.htm" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow">during Q1 2026</a>, sharply lower than the $2.3 million it recorded in 2025 as the deal moved through legal and regulatory processes.</p>



<p>From the February 27 closing date through March 31, the acquired business contributed revenue and gross profit that were “not material,” <a href="https://d3r2gobaqkqkis.cloudfront.net/files/dlocal_1q26_transcript_webcast_presentation_vf.pdf" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow">according to Arnt</a>.</p>



<p>“To be very upfront, the transaction is not material or meaningful in the results that we have just announced,” Arnt said on the <a href="https://d3r2gobaqkqkis.cloudfront.net/files/dlocal_1q26_transcript_webcast_presentation_vf.pdf" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer noopener nofollow">earnings call</a>. “And that has a lot to do with a number of legal and regulatory hurdles that we faced prior to being able to close. I am glad we have crossed that finish line, but in that time period, the deal structure mutated a lot.”</p>



<p>Yet, even in its reduced form, the acquisition gives dLocal something difficult to build quickly in Africa: regulated infrastructure, local market access and embedded operational relationships in a strategically important region.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
					
		
		
